{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"match","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"stringLength"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"string"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"stringReversed"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Passing the correct"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"length of the string given is mandatory. The reversed string can be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"omitted by passing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"text":", this is more efficient if the reversed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"version of the string to be matched is not at hand, as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.PatternSpec.match"},{"text":"] will only construct it if the compiled pattern","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"requires reverse matches.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that, if the user code will (possibly) match a string against a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"multitude of patterns containing wildcards, chances are high that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"some patterns will require a reversed string. In this case, it’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"more efficient to provide the reversed string to avoid multiple","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"constructions thereof in the various calls to [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.PatternSpec.match"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note also that the reverse of a UTF-8 encoded string can in general"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not be obtained by [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.strreverse"},{"text":"]. This works only if the string","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"does not contain any multibyte characters. GLib offers the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.utf8_strreverse"},{"text":"] function to reverse UTF-8 encoded strings.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PatternSpecRef\/match(stringLength:string:stringReversed:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Matches a string against a compiled pattern."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/patternspecref\/match(stringlength:string:stringreversed:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLib","externalID":"s:4GLib19PatternSpecProtocolPAAE5match12stringLength0F00F8ReversedSbSi_SPys4Int8VGSgAKtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib14PatternSpecRefV","title":"match(stringLength:string:stringReversed:)","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text